  "bio": [
    "Zhao jianhui is the chairman of Epiworld International, a maker of silicon carbide (SiC) epitaxial wafers used in power devices for sectors such as EV, renewable energy and AI.",
    "It is the world's largest SiC epitaxial foundry by both revenue and sales volume, accounting for roughly a third of the global market in 2024.",
    "Zhang founded the company in 2011 and took it public on the Hong Kong stock exchange in March 2026.",
    "Zhang has over 35 years of research experience and is the first IEEE Fellow selected based on their contributions to SiC technologies.",
    "He serves as chair professor at Xiamen University in China and worked with Rutgers University in the U.S."
